FULL SYSTEM BLUEPRINT: Manitoba Offender & Missing Person Alert System

ğŸ§© Purpose

A modular system to:

1. Monitor public sources for missing persons and offender releases.


2. Store, classify, and verify alerts in Neo4j.


3. Notify subscribed clients and public users safely.


4. Provide community-sensitive features for First Nations and Indigenous communities.




---

1ï¸âƒ£ Internal App (Private / Core System)

Responsibilities:

Scraping / Parsing: Pulls data from WPS, RCMP, news feeds, RSS.

Classification: Tags events as Missing Person, Offender Release, or News Alert.

Storage: Inserts nodes and relationships in Neo4j.

Verification: Admin dashboard for verifying alerts, flagging incorrect info.

Notification Trigger: Sends SMS via Twilio or push notifications (to internal or public subscribers).

Admin Controls: Full access to historical alerts, trends, and audit logs.


Neo4j Schema (Core + Community Enhancements):

(:Agency { name, url })
(:Event { type, date, source_url, verified, content_level })
(:Person { name, age, community, status })
(:Community { name, region, type })
(:User { phone, preferences, community_subscribed })
(:Service { name, url, type })

Relationships:
(Agency)-[:REPORTED]->(Event)
(Event)-[:INVOLVES]->(Person)
(Event)-[:RELEVANT_TO]->(Community)
(User)-[:SUBSCRIBED_TO]->(Community)
(Alert)-[:SOURCE]->(Service)


---

2ï¸âƒ£ Community-Sensitive Enhancements

Community Filtering: Alerts sent only to relevant regions/communities.

Content Sensitivity: Options for full/high-level alert details; disclaimers for incomplete info.

Privacy & Security: Encrypted user data, opt-in/opt-out controls.

Verification: Flagging and approval by community coordinators.

Accessibility: SMS for low-internet users, optional push notifications.

Optional Cultural Features: Community notice board, Indigenous language messages, support service links.



---

3ï¸âƒ£ Public App (Community-Facing)

Responsibilities:

Subscriptions for community members.

Receives filtered and sanitized alerts via secure endpoints from the internal app.

Sends SMS / push notifications to subscribers.

Displays only community-relevant data; no sensitive info exposed.


Flow:

User subscribes â†’ Requests alerts â†’ Internal App API filters & sanitizes â†’ Alerts delivered via SMS / Push


---

4ï¸âƒ£ Client/Internal App (Hybrid for Coordinators)

Internal clients access the full alert system.

Can verify alerts, manage communities, view trends.

Uses same internal endpoints with full permissions.



---

5ï¸âƒ£ Communication via Secure Endpoints

Public app consumes only filtered data from internal app endpoints.

Protects the database from direct access.

Enables authentication, rate-limiting, logging, and auditing.



---

